added.title: Fast Friends
added.description: While Kana and Thomas deliver aquarium materials for the Vicarstown Fish Day, it's up to steady Percy and Nia to deliver the fish themselves. However, Nia gets a wobbly wheel, inciting Percy to ask Kana for a switch so she can help Nia and speed up the delivery. Once Nia is fixed, she's raring to go, but Kana unexpectedly wants to slow things down to keep the fish safe. Could this quarrel spell doom for the delivery or allow these engines to learn something they never realized about each other?
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Carly's Magnificent Magnet
added.description: When Carly gets a new magnet to help Tess the Troublesome Crane load up a shipment of metal crates, she struggles with the new tool. Carly is frustrated that she's making mistakes during the job. Sandy and Thomas reassure Carly that she needs give herself time to be bad at it. Mistakes are part of learning something new! When Sandy ends up careening towards the water, Carly will have to put her new knowledge to the test and hope she won't make another mistake.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: New Mail Engine in Town
added.description: After Percy gets in an accident and ends up with a broken axle, Nia temporarily takes over his mail delivery duties for him - and her mail delivery is even quicker! Percy thinks the replacement is permanent. In an attempt to find his new thing, Percy tries out different jobs all over Sodor, but nothing seems to fit him quite right. When he's just about ready to give up and head to the mainland, everyone agrees quick is not better. They all miss Percy's caring, careful way of delivering the mail. He's the best engine for the job!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Carly's Screechy Squeak
added.description: Carly has developed a terrible SQUEAK, and Sandy finds an oil can to give her as a feel-good surprise. But when everyone keeps telling Sandy how awful Carly's squeak actually sounds, Sandy feels motivated to keep making the fix bigger and bigger until she's created a wacky robot oil can squirter. The robot goes haywire, squirting everyone except Carly with oil. In the end, Sandy learns that the simple oil can was the only thing Carly needed all along.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Blackout!
added.description: When a storm knocks out power for the whole island, Thomas volunteers to deliver a generator from Kellsthorpe to Knapford. He's determined to complete this task on his own and initially refuses all offers of help, but he soon becomes overwhelmed with complications. Sandy and Carly show up to teach Thomas that everyone needs a little help sometimes, and the three watch as all the engines on Sodor team up to complete the delivery.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Brand New Track
added.description: Thomas and Percy explore a brand-new track the evening before the route is opened. Everything seems new and exciting, and even a night spent stuck in the mud turns into a wonderful experience. Only in the light of day do they realize that nothing they saw was really "new" at all - it just seemed so because they brought to it a sense of delight and discovery.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Stink Monster
added.description: Thomas and the other young engines encounter a stink monster that threatens to spread a stench all over Knapford! When Percy is kidnapped by the stink monster, the rest of the Biggest Adventure Club band together to create a plan to save their friend and stop the stink monster in its tracks! Looking closer, they realize it's their good friend Whiff's new invention causing a stink!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Thomas in Charge
added.description: When Gordon is given an all-day responsibility on the far side of Sodor, he recruits Thomas to be the temporary "Engine in Charge." Even though he advises Thomas about the importance of listening to his team, Thomas assigns tasks to Nia, Diesel, Percy, and Kana that do not match their strengths. With Sandy and Carly as backup, Thomas must fix his errors, use Gordon's advice, and make sure everyone's deliveries are complete before the end-of-day whistle!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Tunnel Troubles
added.description: Sir Topham Hatt has two exciting announcements: it is time for the beautiful Butterfly Migration AND there is a new unnamed express tunnel ready for the first engine to pass through! Thomas and Diesel ask Sir Topham Hatt to hold a race where the winner's name will become the official name of the new tunnel. When both ambitious engines get stuck in the tunnel during the race, they stubbornly refuse to move... even if it risks missing the Butterfly Migration with their friends!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Rocket's Fall
added.description: Thomas learns that the rocket he helped deliver is finally falling back to Earth, into the ocean outside Sodor. Bulstrode, Carly, and their team of retrieval experts are on the job to fish the rocket out of the water, and Thomas wants to help! However, Thomas is so interested in seeing the rocket again that he's too distracted to hear instructions. After a series of mishaps, Thomas learns how to genuinely pay attention, but the rocket is floating towards the drawbridge. Thomas will need to figure out how to help in the best way he knows how before the rocket is lost forever.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Details? What Details?
added.description: After Sir Topham Hatt messes up his instructions for Kenji's passenger delivery, Thomas is asked to set things right! However, as Thomas follows Kenji's trail, he repeatedly forgets to ask his friends for specific directions, preventing him from catching up to the speedy electric engine. Realizing he has to pay more attention to details, Thomas uses his wits, listening skills, and the help of his friends to make it to Kenji and get the passengers to their destinations on time. .
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Blue Engine Blues
added.description: After getting through a rough night's sleep and finding out his beach day gets cancelled due to the rain, Thomas winds up in the grumpiest of moods. Encountering Riff and Jiff with their usual happy-go-lucky attitudes, Thomas comes to the conclusion that he'll only be liked when he appears happy. He puts on fake smile for the rest of the day, but his words don't match his demeanor and everyone can see right through him. Finally, Thomas comes across Riff and Jiff again, who reveal they're also upset about the cruddy day! They teach him that nobody can be happy all the time, and sometimes you need a friend to vent to on the days you're most blue.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: The Case of the Missing Crane
added.description: When Carly does not return from saving Emily from an accidental derailing, a worried Sandy recruits the help of a bored Diesel to find her best gal pal. The unlikely pair become detectives, traveling throughout the island in search of clues. Will they be able to solve the mystery of the missing crane?
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Bad Luck Boxcar
added.description: When Thomas and Percy must transport an unlucky boxcar of bananas, Thomas seems to have bad luck. Percy's positive attitude helps Thomas see the luck in each scenario, breaking the myth of the curse for a successful delivery.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Not So Easy-Greasy
added.description: Nia is nervous about working with Tess, the fastest -- and bossiest -- crane on Sodor! When Nia's plan for a safe and speedy delivery goes awry and causes Tess' wheels to clog with sand, they recruit handy Sandy to solve their problem. Luckily, Sandy has a new invention to get Tess up and going again: a tanker full of her Super-Slick Easy-Greasy Crane Grease! However, chaos continues to ensue when Nia gets stuck in the mud and the runaway grease spills all over Sodor! In the midst of the madness, Nia learns how to fix her original plan and save Sodor from slipping and sliding!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: It All Adds Up
added.description: It is a special day for Harold -- the Northern Lights will shimmer over Sodor at sunset! He cannot wait to share this moment with his engine friends on Lookout Mountain. However, Thomas and the gang have a busy day ahead of them, which is impacted by damage to the Sodor Suspension Bridge. Carly and Sandy warn the excited engines that they should only cross the bridge in case of an emergency -- a rule that is ignored by Kana, Diesel, Nia, AND Thomas! When the bridge finally collapses and prevents them from reaching Lookout Mountain in time, Harold selflessly chooses to help his friends instead of see the Lights. His sacrifice teaches the young engines an important lesson: your actions add up - stay away until it is safe to play.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Bruno's Map Mishap
added.description: Bruno is beyond delighted -- he has received the gift of an updated map of Sodor from Sir Topham Hatt! He and Thomas can't wait to use it to navigate their busy schedule for the day. But when Kana's speedy whoosh blows Bruno's beloved map up, up, and away, Thomas and Bruno team up with Percy and Diesel to recover it! While searching the island far and wide for Bruno's prized possession, the gang discovers that there is something more important than keeping their schedules -- their friendship!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Seeking a Safer Sodor
added.description: After a near-collision rattles their wheels, Percy and Kana enlist the help of Emily to introduce new safety measures all over Sodor. However, their anxiousness about accidents push Percy and Kana to ridiculous extremes that only makes more trouble! When Percy has another accident caused by his off-the-rails safety obsession, he refuses to leave Tidmouth Sheds. When he has to leap into action to help his friends, Percy learns that paying attention to your surroundings is the best way to not have an accident.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: A Cranky Goodbye
added.description: When Bulstrode excitedly announces that he is getting a brand new paint job on the Mainland, everyone is thrilled for him -- except for a crankier-than-usual Cranky. When the crane's dismissive comments upset Bulstrode, the tugboat storms off, leaving Thomas and Percy to pick up the pieces, repair their friendship, and encourage both of them to do something they have never done before -- talk about their true feelings towards each other!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Thomas for a Day
added.description: It's a blustery day on Sodor and Percy finds that his preferred route is closed! He must journey into Crumble Canyon -- a place that makes him terribly nervous! But before he can face his fears, Diesel blasts by, bonking his cargo of blue paint all over the jittery mail engine! Percy is unrecognizable as himself -- instead, he looks just like Thomas! His impromptu makeover inspires Percy to be brave just like his best loco-migo -- and pretend to be the Number One Engine for the day! When Whiff loses his glasses, Percy escorts him across the island and learns that the bravery isn't in the blue paint -- it's inside him!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: The Super Axle
added.description: Sodor welcomes a new engine to the group -- Toby the Tram Engine! Thomas, Diesel, Kana, and the other loco-migos are eager to include their new friend in their deliveries and assigned duties. But as he shadows them, their jobs prove to be a bit too intense for the older engine -- in fact, Toby glumly starts to believe maybe he is too old. Determined to pick up Toby's spirits, Thomas and Sandy get creative and turn an old axle into a "superaxleatortron" -- a 'brand-new' part to put the pep back in Toby's confidence! When the plan goes sideways because the other engines want "super-axles" too, Toby discovers that he never needed the special part -- he just needed to believe in himself!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: The Waiting Game
added.description: Bruno and Nia are tasked with teaming up to help someone very special to the savvy brake car -- a mechanic! But when Bulstrode and his wrench shipment are delayed, it sends Bruno into an agitated tail-spin. To soothe their friend, the engines decide to pass the time by playing the ultimate Waiting Game and learning how to have fun while daydreaming, anticipating, and practicing patience!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go
